events.name: Sofia x Sifa Met/Not Met check

parameters: I was starting to think you wouldn't show...
You were nervous about ME standing YOU up?
That's funny, Ms. K... But it's good to know you were
*COUGH* So anyway... What’s on the docket today?
No, I’m determined to prove to you that, yes, I CAN be
adventurous when I desire. So I've chosen something a bit
As soon as the captain I hired decides to show up!
Diving, eh? Haven't tried it, but it sounds like an
awesome afternoon. Have you done anything like this before?
This will be a new experience for me as well.
I... Didn’t wish to try this alone.
Then I’m glad I could help you try something new.
Hey, I think I see a ship coming!
... You sure this is our boat?
It didn’t look like this in the ad...
“A woman in every port! Laughing an' drinking by the quart!
Busty an' big, they polish my twig!”...
“Then gasp at my ugly wart!” Hahahaha!!!
That would be CAPTAIN to you, Lad.
Captain Timothy B. Shivers, at your humble service.
Mist-... Captain Shivers, are you certain this ship is...
Up to code? I feel misled by your online reservation.
Ahhh, that website be worth every penny I owe. Too many
judge a vessel by the rust in her quarters, I tells ya.
The old girl has seen many seasons and storms,
certainly, but hasn’t done me wrong yet!
So we departin’ or what? The deposit be non-refundable.
We’re here, might as well give this a shot, right..?
I’m fine with whatever you decide, Brenda.
*Sigh*... This better be worth our time, Captain.
That’s the spirit, Lass! Let’s be on our way.
use busts over blurred ship BG
So... Captain Shivers, is there a safety video or, like,
some kind of training we have to do before we jump in?
What he means is have you done this before in your life,
and do you even have a license?
HAHA! Gettin’ the jitters already, are we?
Don’t you two worry none, yer in good hands
Pay no mind how I make a livin’. You won’t find a better
man helming a ship in these waters. Divin’ ain’t nothin’,
just put on a mask and sink.
Wait, you do know how to swim, don’t ya?
Where did you find this guy again..?
This is the last time I take a coffee shop flier...
Bah! Divin’, fishin’, smugglin’, tis all the same!
You’ll get yer money’s worth, believe you me.
Besides... It ain’t me you need to be worryin’ about...
Err... What would we need to worry about then?
There’s a demon under these waters, Lad.
An unholy behemoth that can swallow a man whole...
This oughta work. We can drop anchor here.
Here ya are. Yer paid for the hour, dive safe now.
A-And you’re absolutely positive this is safe..?
<Wow, I don’t think I’ve ever seen Brenda nervous like this
before. Not that I can blame her given our “expert”...>
We don’t have to do this if you don’t want to, Brenda.
There are other things we can do for your book.
I didn’t come all this way on this ridiculous,
floating death-trap just to get cold feet...
The sooner we go, the sooner we get away from this idiot...
Watch the first step, she be a doozy!
use busts over blurred ship BG
OH MY GOD, I DID IT! \N[001], YOU’RE ALIVE!
T-There was a shark... I was stuck...
A-And I was out of air... T-Then you-
*COUGH* You could try some more CPR, if you want..?
Idiot...Don’t scare me like that again!!
Lucky ya survived, I had ta fish ya out the sea...
We’ve had enough excitement for one day, Captain.
Your equipment sucks, and we’re lucky things turned
*Whisper* Plus we totally have a lawsuit here,
and I MAY be able to convince her not to press charges.
Refunding her money would go a long way...
Hm... I don't be wanting any more dealings with the law
than I need. Ol' Timmy can't go to jail again...
Consider this trip on me! I’ll also throw in a
half-off coupon for shrimp! Whatdaya say, Lass?
use busts over blurred ship BG
Thank you for choosing me for all yer nautical needs!
I’m fine, \N[001]. I just want to take a hot shower,
then go home. We’re done for today...
... Thank you for coming with me today...
For... Anyways, I'll take the first shower
stall, you can use the second.
<She’s been through a lot. Better give her
some space, it’s been a hell of a day.>
<Fuck, I think I left my phone on the boat.
Better grab it before Shivers sets sail with it.>

If player is to the left of Sofia, obstructed by the bench
Hey Sof- Mrs. Smyth, hi Sifa!
Of course I do, he’s a student in my afternoon class.
We have a couple classes together, but we met during
Someone was... being rude to me,
and Sifa helped talk me through it.
D’awww, Sifa! My sweet girl, that makes me so proud to hear!
Aw, it wasn’t that big a deal, it was the first day of
school, for both of us, and it didn’t feel right for his
to go badly like that, so I...
She was sweet, and kind, and caring.
Like I’m sure she always is.
So \n[1], you come here a lot too?
Not often, no. My family used to, when I was a kid,
but now... No, I’m just hanging out, might play some
Saturdays are “Mother-Daughter Date-Day”, we usually come
here and hang out at the beach, then have dinner or see a
Time moves so fast, I just want some moments together
so we don’t grow apart as she grows up, y’know?
I think that's a great idea! Making time for
Aw, see Sifa? \n[1] feels the same.
Well, I won’t keep you guys - have a great evening!
\n[1], can you get a pic of us?
We don’t run into friends often, it’d be nice to
have something to remember the day...
It's fine, he can text it to you later Sweetie!
No no, I’d love to. Sounds fun. Here, let me-
Oh, one sec - I don't want to look like
an old lady in it, lemme get ready!
We're at the beach Sifa, it's fine!
That'll make for a good phone background...
I shouldn’t interrupt their day together.
Hey, what're they doing selling an Espectra comic here?
Sweet. Issue number five - the Bloomerang...
Hm... No one's working the booth right now, but it says
if you win the ring toss you can pick a prize...
